                <head>No. 578.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L. S. Sackville West</persName> to
                        Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-05-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 21, 1888</date>. (Received May
                        22.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am informed by the Marquis of Salisbury that a
                    number of Indians from Metlakahtla, in British Columbia, under the leadership of
                    a Mr. William Duncan, formerly a lay missionary of the Church Missionary
                    Society, have withdrawn from that point, and that from information received have
                    settled within the territory of Alaska.</p>
                <p>It is presumed that such immigration and settlement is not contrary to the
                    immigration laws of the United States.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">L. S. Sackville West.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
